text=:Category: LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild%0a:Essential: {Category.LinguisticDiscriminationInTheWild$:essential}%0a:Title: Steven Crowder Discriminating against AAVE%0a:Author: JacobF%0a:Section: A%0a:Completed: 17.04.2021 - 20:18%0a:Status: complete%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a----%0a%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Grading History'''%0a%0a[[#history]]%0a#foxbegin 210504-191848-819980#%0a* [-04.05.2021 - 12:18-] || TA_audrey marked as complete%0a#foxend 210504-191848-819980#%0a[[#historyend]]%0a%0a%25blue%25 '''Comments for student'''%0a%0a[[#comments]]%0a%0a[[#commentsend]]%0a%0a----%0a----%0a!!%0a%0aSummary: \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aSteven Crowder adopts a stereotypical AAVE accent to discriminate against AAVE speakers%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aContent warning: the following article and link contain references to multiple racist stereotypes and caricatures of African-Americans%0a%0aIn the following link, right-wing political commentator Steven Crowder is reacting to a video detailing a bill passed by the Biden administration which allocates $5.2 billion dollars to farmers of color. %0a%0ahttps://twitter.com/JasonSCampbell/status/1371856007203336194%0a%0aCrowder feels, for a variety of ignorant and ill-formed reasons, that the bill is ridiculous, and in place of attempting any sort of real analytical rebuttal, instead adopts a stereotypical AAVE accent and begins a bizarre 'impression' of what he imagines a farmer of color to be. Elements of his own impersonation he seems to place particular emphasis on are his renderings of dental fricatives as alveolar plosives, i.e. th-stopping (ex pronouncing 'that' as [dæt]), and his final consonant deletion (ex pronouncing 'motherfucker' as [məðɐfəkɐ]), both of which are features in AAVE accents.%0a%0a%0aThough he does not explicitly reference his own impersonation as being ungrammatical, it is clear through both his frequent use of racist stereotypes of African-Americans (he and his friends mention trying to plant a 'Hennessy Tree' and an issue with dirt being rendered infertile due to 'a high level of meth') and his overall opinion that the bill is a bad idea, that he is coding this speech as ungrammatical and 'evidence' of low intelligence. Crowder intends for his viewers to see his impression and grammar as 'clear proof' that farmers of color do not know how to farm, and that any money given to them would be wasted.%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a(:GradedBy: TA_audrey:)
